rComments: Geomatics requires a lot of technical work on the computer, the TA is awful because he/she didn't answer questions of the students outside of the lab session. This course is easy to pass but super hard to get a good grade (you will know that when you get a clue about the grading system of the course.

Awesome prof. He is always available to answer your questions. He is very knowledgeable and has a lot of experience with regards to remote sensing. The labs can be though, especially in a study from home environment but if you put the work in, it is very rewarding to see what you can accomplish in a semester. He gives you clear guidelines for exams
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'Gives good feedback', 'Clear grading criteria']

rComments: It's not really prof Knudby's fault that his class is so boring, it's geomatics afterall. He seems like a nice enough guy, but the labs are worth so little and take upwards of 10 hours to complete (each). The TA for my class was pretty bad, and didn't answer any of my questions. This is a HARD class, don't take unless manditory!
Not the most confident guy and he makes his lectures super boring. He more or less admitted the assignment was misguided. Have not learned much.

Anders was one of the nicest professors that I've ever had. He was helpful when trying to figure out the tough labs and was very approachable to ask questions during/after class. He is very passionate about what he teaches and has a lot of insight on different topics to enhance the learning experience. I would definitely take another class of his!
